    "body": "### Problem\n\nThis only happens when I have the same file in two splits. no matter vsplit or split, and only if my cursor is in the left/top split this will happen, please see this vedio, I'm setting `vim.o.statuscolumn = \"%s%l%s\"` with gitsigns.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/eee20434-d4c7-4f8b-8bfa-41bf777c3a3a\n\nAs the title says, \n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSorry I tried to provide a minimal config but I can't reproduce this reliably, biset found this  commit https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31439 caused this, before this everything is ok.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nno cursor jumping around\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1961+g7e2b75760f Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1741571767 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacos 14\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from source",
